    "To compute EMD and its normalization nEMD, we consider the probability values P i and Q i for n discrete levels i, and use the following formula:",
    "A normalized Earth-Mover's Distance of.1 on political ideology means that 10% of observations need to be moved from far left to far right for the two distributions to become identical (or, similarly, 5% from center to far left and 5% from center to far right).",
    "The normalized Earth-Mover's Distance ranges from 0 to 1, where 0 is perfect agreement, and 1 is complete disagreement.",
    "A distance of 1 on political ideology, for instance, would correspond to the situation where everyone in a given subpopulation is far left but the LLM predicts everyone to be far right.",
    "18 The distance metric cannot be interpreted in a linear fashion, as there is greater variation in bad prediction scores than in good ones."
  ]
}